<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="610" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[2066,2660,1833,2256]" lastBlockId="13.[1451,2657,2262,2688]" pageId="13" pageNumber="610">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2066,2346,2184,2218]" pageId="13" pageNumber="610">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 118-134 mm, tail 59-85 mm, ear 16-H-20-7 mm, hindfoot 21-23 mm; weight 33-58 g. Makundi’s Brush-furred Rat has speckled pelage and a rather shorttail. It has significantly smaller hindfeet and longertail length than Verhagen’s Brush-furred Rat (
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. Verheyen, Hulselmans, Dierckx &amp; E. Verheyen" authorityYear="2002" box="[2044,2209,2340,2374]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Lophuromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="13" pageNumber="610" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="verhageni">L. verhageni</taxonomicName>
), smaller head-body length and longer ears than the Dark-colored Brush-furred Rat (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="True" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[2200,2339,2383,2412]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Lophuromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="13" pageNumber="610" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aquilus">L. aquilus</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
